Check ubuntu version :
1. lsb_release -a
2. Alternate : cat /etc/lsb-release

**How to check os version in Linux command line**
1. hostnamectl

Type the following command to find Linux kernel version:
uname -r

To list all local users you can use:
cut -d: -f1 /etc/passwd

Ubuntu create user account commands (https://askubuntu.com/questions/410244/a-command-to-list-all-users-and-how-to-add-delete-modify-users)
sudo adduser gauravjain448

To get root access.
1. sudo -i 
2. sudo su -

#, indicating that you have root access.
command exit to leave the root shell.













